#Write a Python function that solves the problem: "Colby loves going to the movies and every month his parents give him $150 to spend at the movies. Tickets for Fridays and Saturdays cost $10. Tickets for any other day cost $7. Popcorn costs $8 and boxes of candy cost $2. It is the last day of the month and it's a Friday. He wants to make sure he gets a popcorn and box of candy that night. How many movies can he see if he already saw 5 movies on a Friday or Saturday, 8 movies on other days, had 2 tubs of popcorn, and four boxes of candy that month?"
def tickets(popcorn, candy, friday, saturday, other):
    if friday + saturday + other < 5:
        return 0
    if popcorn < 2:
        return 0
    if candy < 4:
        return 0
    if friday + saturday > 8:
        return 0
    return friday + saturday + other - 5 + (popcorn-2)*2 + (candy-4)*2
#Call the function tickets to solve the problem: "Colby loves going to the movies and every month his parents give him $150 to spend at the movies. Tickets for Fridays and Saturdays cost $10. Tickets for any other day cost $7. Popcorn costs $8 and boxes of candy cost $2. It is the last day of the month and it's a Friday. He wants to make sure he gets a popcorn and box of candy that night. How many movies can he see if he already saw 5 movies on a Friday or Saturday, 8 movies on other days, had 2 tubs of popcorn, and four boxes of candy that month?"
