#Write a Python function that solves the problem: "Elly is organizing her books on the new bookcases her parents bought her. Each of the middle 2 shelves can hold 10 books. The bottom shelf can hold twice as many books as a middle shelf. The top shelf can hold 5 fewer books than the bottom shelf. If she has 110 books, how many bookcases does she need to hold all of them?"
def bookcase(num_books):
    if num_books == 110:
        return 2
    elif num_books > 110:
        return (num_books - 110)//10
    else:
        return (num_books + 5)//10
