#Write a Python function that solves the problem: "Dr. Hugo Grumpus and his assistant, Igor, were preparing to perform a laboratory experiment.  Dr. Grumpus told Igor to gather 16 test tubes, 7 beakers, and 14 Petri dishes, and to place them all on the lab bench.  By accident, Igor gathered half as many test tubes as requested, two more than the number of Petri dishes requested.  And while he had picked up the correct number of beakers, he lost several on the way to the lab bench.  In total, the number of items Igor had placed on the lab bench was 29.  How many beakers did Igor lose?"
def solve_dr_grumpus(t,b,p):
    if (t - b) == (p - 1):
        return "Igor lost {} beakers.".format(b - t)
    elif (t + b) == (p + 1):
        return "Igor lost {} test tubes.".format(t - p)
    else:
        return "Igor lost {} test tubes and {} beakers.".format(t - p, b - t)
#Call the function solve_dr_grumpus to solve the problem: "Dr. Hugo Grumpus and his assistant, Igor, were preparing to perform a laboratory experiment.  Dr. Grumpus told Igor to gather 16 test tubes, 7 beakers, and 14 Petri dishes, and to place them all on the lab bench.  By accident, Igor gathered half as many test tubes as requested, two more than the number of Petri dishes requested.  And while he had picked up the correct number of beakers, he lost several on the way to the lab bench.  In total, the number of items Igor had placed on the lab bench was 29.  How many beakers did Igor lose?"
